# This tree is a BYTE-OF-RECORD. Git must never rewrite a byte of it.
#
# Each upstream historicalsource repo shipped its own `.gitattributes` with
# `* text=auto`, and vendoring dragged them in — which handed git permission to
# "auto-detect" and line-ending-normalize our ROM images. It got away with it only
# because ALEXEC.LDA/SNDAUX.LDA/the numbered dumps happen to contain NUL bytes, so
# the heuristic guessed binary. A NUL-free ROM, or a checkout with
# core.autocrlf=true, and the audit's oracle would be silently rewritten underneath
# it — `just extract-audio` compares these bytes against the ROM.
#
# So: no eol conversion, ever, for anything in here. Text stays the LF-normalized
# ASCII that vendorBytes() produced; binaries stay verbatim.
* -text
